What a great spot up here in the montrose area. I was blown away by the deliciousness of my BLAT. On sourdough bread I got bacon, lettuce, avocado and tomato. Comes with a very very very good house salad. Very fulfilling, pretty much the perfect amount of food. Pricing, IMO, is decent and worth it. Love it here, will definitely be back.

Please don't eat here on less you want salmonella and egg shells in your fried rice. I ordered from this place twice and both time my rice has had egg shells. They also don't care if you have a shellfish allergy because i told them to make my rice and noodles shrimp less but they only got part of that right.
Good price and a lot food

My husband ordered a honey garlic chicken dinner meal and a lg order of special fried rice without soy sauce. Once it got delivered the lg special fried rice was covered in soy sauce I called the restaurant and the lady told me I’m wrong the reason the rice is brown is because of other sauces they use when I asked what sauce did they use I got no reply. My husband tried the rice and said that it tastes like soy sauce. Clearly they messed up instead of owning it and trying to find a resolution they rather have a first time customer leave a delightful review. I’ve ordered the special fried rice in many restaurants and guess what the rice is white not brown because of other sauces they use.

I have had NY Chinese at hunts point, I've had chinese in other parts of florida, Cali, central US, and in the southwest/northeast. I consider myself somewhat of an American Chinese addict... This is hands down THE best Chinese food restaurants I have ever had.. If you are new to the area it is a must try! P.s. no need for extra chicken, the plate they give you on the dinner combo could feed an army! Also the crab rangoons are amazing. Excellent customer service as well, only downfall was the non English speaking delivery driver as I dont know any Spanish.
Great food! Highly recommended.
